## Trickier algebraic identities

Two more advanced problems drawn from the standard equational benchmarks: each
is purely first-order, each has a short paramodulation proof, and each forces
the Leibniz machinery to enumerate substantial chunks of the term universe.

**`(xy)⁻¹ = y⁻¹ x⁻¹`** — group inverse of a product.

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      #{group_axioms}
      thf(conj, conjecture,
        ![X:$i, Y:$i]: i @ (o @ X @ Y) = o @ (i @ Y) @ (i @ X)).
      """,
      Keyword.put(opts, :timeout, 15_000)
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

